RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 7F Turf CR: 82. Claiming Purse 40200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 6 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEEDY LYNN stalked on the rail near the rear down the backstretch, angled outside circling runners with five sixteenths remaining, continued to pass foes seven deep straightening out for the drive finding her best stride in mid stretch and drew away comfortably at the finish. A GAL FOR T J broke out at the start, tracked in the middle of the pack between runners two off the fence with five eighths to run, rallied six wide at the quarter marker, lost path in lane four at the furlong pole, switched outside and closed to just get up for the runners up share crossing the line. VERY SAVVY was brushed inside at the break, tracked the pacesetter three wide outside throughout the turn, assumed the lead turning for home in the three path, was headed outside in upper stretch and battled inside holding for the show award at the end. LINCOLNVILLE BEACH travelled on the rail in mid field down the back straight, stalked inside unhurried through the turn, commenced a run slipping up the fence then shifted out four deep at the top of the stretch to bid for the front, stalled in deep stretch and had to settle for a minor role in the end. FORESTERS PRINCESS was in a good position tracking the early leader in the two path into the turn, was urged left handed three furlongs from home, offered little response and made no impact driving to the wire. HALO STYLE broke outwards to begin, settled in midpack four deep down the backstretch, stalked four well outside runners throughout the turn making little advance and could not be a factor in the stretch run. CEDAR VALLEY hopped at the start trailing down the backside, shifted outside at the half mile marker, was fanned out to the eight path straightening out for the stretch run and could not reach contention running to the wire. NADIABIZNIZ took command from the start, continued to dictate the pace on the turn, was collared at the top of the lane and backed away on the fence in upper stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 2 1 1/16M Inner turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 51000. INNER TURF FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 6 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $23,500, allowed 1 lb. (Races Where En tered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HULLABALOO took control from the start to clear the field into the first turn, was left alone unchallenged down the backside, scooted for home at the top of the lane and had enough left in reserve to hold safe at the wire. CANYOUHEARMENOW was nestled on the rail keeping a close eye on the leader down the backstretch in the second flight, took up the chase going after the lone pacesetter two furlongs from the finish, could not close the gap on the winner through the stretch and had to settle for second best on this day. JMR PURE SENSATION hopped at the break to trail the field down the back straight, waited inside behind runners on the final turn, continued to save ground turning for home and offered a late sustained run on the fence to capture third in the end. OCTOBER FROST travelled in the middle of the pack on the fence with a half mile to go, waited on the rail when the field bunched up three furlongs from the wire, had clear run in the two path at the top of the lane and finished up to hold for a small share in the end. JUST START ME UP hopped at the start but recovered inside to chase the pace in the beginning, was asked for run between horses to try to reel in the loose front runner midway on the far turn, could not find more and levelled out five wide through the stretch drive. BOX N SCORE was away slowly to begin, travelled near the rear outside at the half mile marker, offered a brief turn of foot circling around foes three furlongs from the finish and was only one paced in the stretch drive to the finish. TOURIST'S DREAM settled four wide in the mid pack in the early stages of the race, rallied four deep three furlongs from the prize, was fanned widest five wide at the top of the stretch and came up empty for the drive to the wire. INFAMOUS COVERT stalked four wide on the first turn, settled near the rear three deep between foes at the half, offered a mild run when roused three furlongs from home until the quarter pole and had little to show in the stretch drive. COPINSAY tracked between runners two wide into the first turn, was ridden to keep position with rivals on either side at the three eighths pole and gave way midpoint on the final turn.

AWESOMECREST broke a half-step slowly, advanced inside near the half under encouragement to get within range of the leader, given more stout urging early on the turn, faltered and faded. TARADAR stalked within close range and shifting in, put to urging between runners two wide late on the turn, faltered and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT ARKLE was in a good spot on the turn not too far of the front group, started to close the gap on the leaders six wide at the three sixteenths pole, had clear run and wore down rivals in deep stretch to narrowly prevail at the finish. NIKOLAOU was relaxed near the back of the field on the rail on the turn, rallied inside to be in range of the leaders turning for home, had nowhere to go behind tiring frontrunners in upper stretch, finally found a seam shifting out five wide at the eighth pole and closed strongly to just miss in the end. BAJAN BULLET was bumped outside on the break, regrouped to have a good position watching the top threesome on the turn, took command four wide at the three sixteenths pole and gave way grudgingly very late to be a clear third at the wire. HARDWARE GAP brushed foe at the start, advanced smartly inside with three furlongs remaining, had clear run on the fence at the top of the lane to be in the hunt at the furlong marker and evened out in deep stretch. BE LIKE CLINT was brushed at the start, trailed the field down the backside and through the turn, still could see most of the field when straightening out for the stretch drive and had good energy to put in a solid closing run to the finish. COLLABORATIVE stalked near the back of the field, continued to save ground inside on the turn and showed some late interest in mid stretch to pass tired runners. PASSTHEPUDDINPLEAZ stalked at the back of the pack three deep outside horses in the beginning, angled out widest in the nine path two furlongs from the wire and finished evenly outside runners in the late stages. MUSKOKA GIANT settled four deep in mid pack down the backside, could not make any headway on the leaders running on the turn, shifted out six wide for the drive but could not get involved driving to the finish line. GUNGI bumped on the break, regrouped quickly to prompted the pace in the early going, tracked the frontrunner on the turn, bid three wide turning for home and retreated between runners in the final furlong. LAKE SHORE DRIVE took the field down the back straight, opened up mildly on the chasers running on the turn, was collared outside with three sixteenths to go and tired inside at the furlong marker. CONFUSING sat three deep just off the contesting pair down the backstretch, continued to track in third throughout the turn, was in the mix for a share four wide at the top of the lane and stopped in mid stretch. ETHNIC SOUL stalked near the back in the early stages, was roused but lost ground inside to rivals throughout the turn and could not pass any horses in the stretch drive.

EMICRACK (CHI) got away well, settled in behind the eventual winner tracking that one racing just off the rail, came out at the top of the stretch for room, loomed a threat in upper stretch, drifted out through mid- to late-stretch, kept on late to be second best. ABOVE PAR was off the early leader then advanced rapidly to press the pacesetter and eventual winner coming to the seven-sixteenths, began to drop back at the quarter pole, drifted out leaving the turn, was bumped near the eighth pole while continuing to weaken and faded. RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 6 6F All Weather Track CR: 77. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 65900. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD ONTARIO SIRED MAIDENS OR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MT LOGAN was reined back inside off the early pace duel at the half, rallied when splitting runners three eighths from the finish, loomed the threat four wide straightening out for the stretch drive and finished strongly to comfortably hold on to the win at the wire. SOUPER SUNSHINE prompted outside entering the turn, bore out with five sixteenths to run, was eight wide at the top of the lane and re-rallied to close in for second money to best the rest. GRAND AMBITION broke outwards on the break, was bumped repeatedly to start to be near the rear down the backstretch, advanced smartly on the rail through the turn, sat behind horses looking for room turning for home, finally found a seam on the fence one hundred yards from the finish and closed in to capture third in gritty overall performance. OLD BLUE CLIFF was bumped around between horses on the start to be near the rear leaving the chute, recovered to be behind the leaders at the half but was a little headstrong, was roused two furlongs from the wire and determinedly finished up to close in for a minor share in the end. CHAIRMAN RAINBOW broke in on rivals at the start, took command with a half mile remaining, opened up mildly on the field with five sixteenths to go, was inside still clinging onto the lead in mid stretch and tired nearing the wire to lose positions late. SO CALLED VACATION settled outside in midfield in the early stages, could not keep up with others through the turn and was one paced in the stretch drive. AMAZON FORESTER pressed the issue inside four furlongs from home, lost some position on the rail running through the turn, did not give up and battled between inside through the stretch and lost his path nearing the wire. SECRET STORM chased behind the frontrunner outside midway on the turn, bid for the lead just outside with a quarter to run and yielded in the three path in mid stretch. MARTEN STORM was slow breaking from the gate, caught up to the field by the half mile marker, continued to keep pace with rivals on the turn, was in the mix for a small share behind horses turning for home and levelled out at the furlong pole. DANCIN' DEPUTY stalked near the rear down the backstretch, was shuffled to last with three furlongs to run and was not a factor running to the finish. JMR SPEEDY ESCAPE was pinballed between rivals to start, steadied sharply leaving the chute to trail the field and could not recover to be involved after that poor beginning. STEWARDS INQUIRY REGARDING THE BEGINNING OF THE RACE RESULTED IN #7 CHAIRMEN RAINBOW BEING DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE WITH #5 JMR ESCAPE AT THE START

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASHBURY stalked in the two path near the rear when the field was bunching into the backstretch at the eleven sixteenths marker, relaxed kindly between horses down the back straight, offered a bold move bursting between rivals two furlongs from home and was full of run in the stretch to draw away when crossing the finish line. TRIZZEL TRAZZEL settled in the middle of the field five deep into the first turn, was under a snug hold outside four wide entering the backstretch, was let out a notch to engage for the lead outside at the half, sat just outside off the contesting leaders on the far turn, pounced to the front turning for home but could not find more to hold off the fast closing winner in deep stretch. ALBERTA BE MINE was off slow at the start, had a good inside position with four furlongs left to run, followed the path set by the winner at the quarter pole and lengthened stride at the top of the lane to close in and be a clear third at the finish line. WAR'S END KISS was bumped on the break, sat just behind the top pair at the half, was nudged on for more midway on the far turn, was in a tight spot between horses in upper stretch, had to wait momentarily at the furlong marker and had clear run late to get up for a minor share. BITTERSWEETBIZNESS was hustled for the lead inside taking the field into the first turn, was headed outside by runners at the half, battled stubbornly holding onto the front through the far turn, was collared straightening out for the drive and levelled out in deep stretch. REINS OF PURPLE was fanned six wide into the first turn, advanced outside runners four or five deep down the backside, continued to gain on the leaders outside while widest in the final turn, was in with a chance for a share at the top of the lane and still willingly drove to the wire to be involved for the minors in the end. SMARTY ILLUSION was unhurried early to see the field into the first turn, settled near the rear with a half left to run, shifted out six wide for the drive to the line and was one paced thru the lane. GOLD FORESTER chased the leader in the early stages, bid for the lead two wide with runners on either side at the quarter marker and faded in mid stretch. TENPENNY NAIL was bumped on the break to be last two wide into the first turn, continued to see the field down the backside and passed stragglers in the stretch run. NORTHERN PASSAGE tracked three wide into the first turn, could not maintain position three deep between runners at the half, was hard ridden on the final turn and was a non factor in the late stages. I'M EXCEPTIONAL was fighting the rider on the rail when trying to relax behind the leaders into the backstretch, continued to be eager inside at the half mile marker, could not keep pace with horses through the far turn on the fence and was empty for the stretch run.
